---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Colors"
  description="The palette of emotions that shape my artistic voice."
  heroImage=""
>
  <div class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
    <p class="text-lg mb-12">
      I choose very few colors.<br />
      I stay with them until they start to speak.<br />
      Limiting the palette makes every shade matter; it turns color from decoration into a way of thinking and feeling.<br />
      The full range of human emotion does not need all colors.<br />
      It needs the right ones, in the right contrasts and quiet harmonies.
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-8">
      <!-- Blue -->
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-0 md:gap-6 items-start">
        <div class="w-48 md:w-1/3 overflow-hidden flex items-start flex-shrink-0">
          <img src="/colors/blues.png" alt="Blue" class="w-full h-auto object-contain object-top !m-0" />
        </div>
        <div class="flex-1">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-0 md:mb-3">Blue</h2>
          <p>The color of distance and depth, of longing and the quiet ache of introspection.<br />
          Blue is the space between what is said and what is felt, holding the vastness of unspoken thoughts.<br />
          I use its entire spectrum, from the palest whisper of sky to the deepest indigo of night, embracing all its moods and meanings.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Gold -->
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-0 md:gap-6 items-start">
        <div class="w-48 md:w-1/3 overflow-hidden flex items-start flex-shrink-0">
          <img src="/colors/gold.png" alt="Gold" class="w-full h-auto object-contain object-top !m-0" />
        </div>
        <div class="flex-1">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-0 md:mb-3">Gold</h2>
          <p>A spark in darkness.<br />
          Hope caught in light.<br />
          Not the gold of excess, but of illumination, the divine glimpsed in the ordinary, the belief that beauty persists even in sorrow.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- White -->
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-0 md:gap-6 items-start">
        <div class="w-48 md:w-1/3 overflow-hidden flex items-start flex-shrink-0">
          <img src="/colors/white.png" alt="White" class="w-full h-auto object-contain object-top !m-0" />
        </div>
        <div class="flex-1">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-0 md:mb-3">White</h2>
          <p>Emptiness that is full.<br />
          Silence that speaks.<br />
          White is the pause that gives everything else meaning, the absence that creates presence.<br />
          It is both surrender and possibility.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Brown -->
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-0 md:gap-6 items-start">
        <div class="w-48 md:w-1/3 overflow-hidden flex items-start flex-shrink-0">
          <img src="/colors/brown.png" alt="Brown" class="w-full h-auto object-contain object-top !m-0" />
        </div>
        <div class="flex-1">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-0 md:mb-3">Brown</h2>
          <p>Earth and roots.<br />
          The warmth of memory worn smooth by time.<br />
          Brown grounds the ethereal in the weight of what is real, a reminder that we are made of dust and will return to it.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
